AB  - Fluoroscopy is a key imaging modality in the pediatric population and can be used to diagnose emergent conditions in the neonatal period, including malrotation with midgut volvulus, and atresias of the small intestine. This activity is designed to teach radiologists about critical portions of the pediatric upper gastrointestinal fluoroscopic examination and to provide an overview of pediatric upper gastrointestinal fluoroscopy for general practitioners to improve confidence and accuracy with diagnosing common and emergent conditions. © 2022 Lippincott Williams and Wilkins. All rights reserved.
